The course will study the applicability of biotechnological processes for e.g. the removal of pollution, generation of renewable energy or production of biomass, by exploiting biological processes, and how to integrate these techniques into the modern economy.
Part of the course will be lectures providing basic theoretical background of main topics and in the second part students will work with case-studies to seek solutions for real-life problems.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of course to give an overview of using biotechnology applications for solving environmental problems and engineering of various organisms for their use in the context of bioeconomy.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students completing the course will gain knowledge in following topics: *	Using various organisms for environmental cleanup and remediation. *	Basic principles of wastewater treatment technologies by microorganisms. *	Use of various organisms for biofuel and biopolymer production. *	Engineering of organisms for efficient energy and resource use. *	European bioeconomy strategies."
